(15, 1, 1, 'Is Bana Hills Worth It? What To Do In Bana Hills 2024-2025', 'Is Bana Hills Worth It? What To Do In Bana Hills 2024-2025', 'Ba Na Hills in Vietnam located in the Truong Son Mountains system near Da Nang, Vietnam, is a destination that effortlessly blends natural beauty, cultural heritage, and great attractions. This place is sought after by guests around the world.', '<h1 class=\"new\">Is Bana Hills Worth It? What To Do In Bana Hills 2024-2025</h1>\r\n<div class=\"blog-post-content\">\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re seeking an exceptional destination to explore upon your arrival in Da Nang, Ba Na Hills is an excellent choice.<br><a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/ba-na-hills-in-vietnam/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Ba Na Hills in Vietnam</strong></a>&nbsp;located in the Truong Son Mountains system near Da Nang, Vietnam, is a destination that effortlessly blends natural beauty, cultural heritage, and great attractions. This place is sought after by guests around the world.<br>When you visit Sun World Ba Na Hills, you&rsquo;ll embark on a unique journey through four seasons in a single day. Glide through the skies on cable cars and immerse yourself in the pristine beauty of Ba Na Nui Chua&rsquo;s ancient forests. Indulge in a wide variety of culinary delights and bask in the festive ambiance.<br><em>Let us show you the reason why we use the great word to describe Ba Na Hills, the greatest place to add to your next trip, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/ba-na-hills-in-vietnam/\"><strong>what to do in Ba Na Hills in 2024</strong></a></em></p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-6.jpg\" alt=\"Is Bana Hills Worth It\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"1\">1. Is Ba Na Hills Worth It?</h3>\r\n<p>With us, the tour operators have many chances to explore Ba Na Hills and with the review of many visitors, who come from all over the world, Ba Na Hills is a great place to visit when you arrive in Da Nang City.<br>Ba Na Hills offers stunning natural landscapes, including lush forests and panoramic views. It will be a worthwhile destination for visitors to enjoy the view from the high mountain.</p>\r\n<p>The climate is cooler than in Da Nang Center, making it a refreshing escape during the hot season. It is a suitable place to enjoy a day with milder temperatures.<br>To explain why we declare that this is a place worth spending time in, let&rsquo;s read the exciting thing below to know why Ba Na Hills is famous.?</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-8.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"2\">2. Ba Na Hills History</h3>\r\n<p>Ba Na Hills, located 30 km from Da Nang and 45-50 km from Hoi An, Vietnam, was originally established as a hill station and relaxing place by the French colonialists in the early 20th century. It is a place with a cool climate, fresh landscapes, and beautiful scenery.<br>During the colonial era, they developed Ba Na Hills into a resort destination, complete with French villages hotels, and entertainment gameshow. The place is famous a reputation as a cool and peaceful escape from the lowland heat.</p>\r\n<p>After the French colonial period and amid the Vietnam War, Ba Na Hills fell into disrepair and was largely abandoned. The resort&rsquo;s infrastructure deteriorated over the years.<br>In the early 21st century, Ba Na Hills was a place of interest for many companies. Sun Group Viet Nam invested in its restoration and modernization, transforming it into a famous tourist destination.</p>\r\n<p>Ba Na Hills has become a renowned tourist destination, attracting visitors from around the world. Its unique blend of natural beauty, cultural heritage, and modern attractions make it a must-visit spot in central Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p>The history of Ba Na Hills reflects its transformation from a colonial-era retreat to a vibrant and captivating tourist destination known for its stunning landscapes and attractions.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-11.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"3\">3. What is there to do in Ba Na Hills?</h3>\r\n<p>There are many things to do in Ba Na hills, you can enjoy the amazing climate there with the thousands of flowers grown around the mountain, and visit the very famous places in this mountain like:</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.1\">3.1 The Golden Bridge ( The Hand Bridge )</h4>\r\n<p>It also known as Cau Vang in Vietnamese, is a remarkable and iconic architectural masterpiece located in the Ba Na Hills, Da Nang, Vietnam.<br>The Golden Bridge is well known for its unique and amazing design. The bridge appears to be held aloft by two huge stone hands emerging from the surrounding hills, giving it a surreal and special quality.</p>\r\n<p>When you stay on this bridge, you see an overview of the lush forests and Da Nang city center from the high mountain with 1414 meters, it is amazing to touch the clouds in the afternoon from this place.</p>\r\n<p>The Bridge blends modern engineering with natural beauty, creating an attraction where you can touch or stand on the clouds and it is a feeling that you stay far away from the mountain, you can go a circle from the Wine Debay to the Flower Garden through the bridge, and return.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you&rsquo;re a nature lover, an architecture enthusiast or just looking for a unique and special destination the Golden Bridge Vietnam is very worth visiting and provides a once-in-a-lifetime experience.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-5.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.2\">3.2 The Garden of Love</h4>\r\n<p>It is called Flower Garden, this place is a captivating and romantic garden located within the Ba Na Hills resort complex, near the Golden Bridge.</p>\r\n<p>If you are looking for a place filled with flowers, there is a great place for you. You can find many types of flowers with unique shapes. And a place in this complex is very exciting the maze garden, it is built with trees and flowers, and you will have an adventure to solve this mysterious maze.</p>\r\n<p>It is also a great place for the couple to take photos at the wedding, and it is very beautiful when you stay at the center of the huge flower garden, how do you think if you can stay between the very huge lavender garden and smell it&rsquo;s.</p>\r\n<p>Visiting the Garden of Love at Ba Na Hills is a delightful experience, offering a peaceful and romantic respite amid the natural beauty of this hill. Whether you&rsquo;re with a loved one or just looking for a tranquil area, this garden provides a serene setting for your visit.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-12.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.3\">3.3 Linh Ung Pagoda</h4>\r\n<p>It is located within the flower garden at Ba Na Hills is a place of spiritual significance and natural beauty.</p>\r\n<p>Linh Ung Pagoda is a serene and spiritually enriching destination. It serves as a place of worship and meditation for Buddhists and offers visitors a sense of tranquility and inner peace.</p>\r\n<p>You will see a huge statue of the Bodhisattva of Mercy standing at the center of the yard which is one of the tallest in Vietnam, standing at over 67 meters (220 feet) in height. The statue exudes a sense of compassion and grace. This statue was built by the best engineer with a unique design and is impressive.</p>\r\n<p>This pagoda is located on the hillside, you can get the beauty scenic from there with the weather amazing, creating a unique and captivating destination.</p>\r\n<p>Visiting Linh Ung Pagoda at Ba Na Hills offers a good chance to explore the spiritual and cultural facets of Vietnam while enjoying the scenic beauty of the surrounding landscape. It&rsquo;s a place to reflect, find inner peace, and live more slowly to know the value of our lives</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/linh-ung-1.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.4\">3.4 Debay Wine Cellar</h4>\r\n<p>The Old Debay Wine was built in 1923 by the French, it is a deep tunnel through Ba Na Mountain, 100m deep, and is always kept at a temperature between 16 and 20 degrees. Visitors are allowed to see anything was happened in the past and have a chance to enjoy the special taste of wine from there.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.5\">3.5 The Wax Museum</h4>\r\n<p>If you only can see the pictures of many figures of historical and famous personalities on the internet or in books, then when you come to the Wax Museum at Ba Na Hills you will see very real shapes, like Michael Jackson, Jackie Chan, Barack Obama president&hellip; this museum is a great place to take the photo with your idol and learn about their contributions to history and culture.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.6\">3.6 The French Village</h4>\r\n<p>The French Village at Ba Na Hills is charming and really poetic to the ambiance of a traditional French town. The village is designed to replicate the architecture, churches, streets, and ambiance of a typical French town, complete with cobblestone streets, quaint buildings, and traditional gates. It exudes Old World charm and European flair.</p>\r\n<p>It is a very strange feeling when you walk into an old French town and enjoy a coffee cup with a cake under streets with cloudy weather.</p>\r\n<p>The village often hosts live cultural performances, adding to the authentic atmosphere. You may encounter street dancers, musicians, and other entertainers as you stroll through its streets.</p>\r\n<p>With its charming architecture and European vibes, this place is a favorite spot for photography. You will have great photos of a French town without leaving Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p>Visiting the French Village at Ba Na Hills allows you to step into a different world, and experience European charm. It is a place you must come in one time of your life.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Alpine Coaster at Ba Na Hills</strong>&nbsp;is an exhilarating and adrenaline-pumping attraction that offers visitors a thrilling ride down the mountainside. But with us, it is waiting for a long time to join this game, and if you are a person who loves architecture you do not have enough time to wait.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Fantasy Park at Ba Na Hills</strong>&nbsp;is located under square, Fantasy Park is a place with a variety of thrilling rides and attractions that cater to visitors of all ages. From bumper cars to roller coasters a 3D,4D, 5D cinema, and climbing unnatural mountains, there&rsquo;s no shortage of excitement.</p>\r\n<p>It does not only provide adrenaline-pumping rides but also offers family-friendly activities, making it a great destination for a day of fun with loved ones, it is a great place to stay after lunch on the trip to Ba Na Hills, you can spend 2 hours exploring these games.</p>\r\n<p>Don&rsquo;t worry about your kids, there&rsquo;s a dedicated kids&rsquo; zone with rides and games tailored to their age group, ensuring a safe and enjoyable experience for children.</p>\r\n<p>They have several stages to host live entertainment shows, performances, and events, create a festive atmosphere, and provide additional entertainment options for visitors.</p>\r\n<p>It is truly a great place to take a rest after lunch before you keep on the trip exploring Ba Na Hills.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Beer Plaza</strong>&nbsp;is designed to create a vibrant and festive atmosphere. It&rsquo;s a place where visitors can unwind, socialize, and enjoy the company of friends and fellow travelers.</p>\r\n<p>You can order many types of beers from this place with cocktails, and non-alcoholic options. It is a great place to sit down for a short time and talk to other guests who visit Ba Na Hills like you. At this place, you can see live performances or themed events, enhancing the overall experience and providing entertainment from Square</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-13.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"4\">4. Food, Drinks &amp; Restaurants</h3>\r\n<p>Don&rsquo;t worry if you think you can&rsquo;t find the food suitable for you at Ba Na Hills, although you are from India, Asia, or the UK, they offer a diverse range of dining options, ensuring that visitors can satisfy their culinary cravings</p>\r\n<p>International Cuisine: it is easy to find restaurants offering a variety of international cuisines, including French, Vietnamese, Italian, and more at French Village. You can enjoy dishes from around the world without leaving the resort.</p>\r\n<p>Vietnamese Cuisine: you can see many Vietnamese traditional favorites like pho, spring rolls, and fresh seafood prepared in a local style, but if you are a local visitor, the buffet lunch is the best for you to enjoy 80 dishes.</p>\r\n<p>Cafes and Bakeries: After the time walking around the Ba Na Hills complex, if you feeling a little tired, stop and take an egg coffee or Vietnamese coffee.</p>\r\n<p>Scenic Dining: Many of the restaurants offer picturesque views of the surrounding mountains and landscapes, providing an unforgettable dining backdrop.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you&rsquo;re in the mood for a casual snack, a gourmet meal, or a refreshing drink, Ba Na Hills provides a wide array of dining options to cater to different tastes and preferences. We highly appreciate their preparation.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/buffe-bana.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"5\">5. Ba Na Hills Festivals</h3>\r\n<p>Ba Na Hills is renowned for its diverse and exciting festivals, offering visitors a wide range of experiences throughout the year.</p>\r\n<p>Beer Festival: if you visit Ba Na Hills at this time, you will see many types of beers from some countries in the world, especially the beers from Germany, stay at the square take a beer or cup, and enjoy the dance performance.</p>\r\n<p>Flower Festival: Ba Na Hills is a place covered by flowers, if you come in during the Flowers Festival, it is amazing. You will see a thousand types of flowers from many countries, like the tulip, rose, sunflower, &hellip;.but hydrangeas are the soul of the festival.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;The Pumpkin Battle in the Kingdom of Sunshine&rdquo;: This unique festival adds a touch of whimsy and playfulness to Ba Na Hills. Visitors can join in pumpkin-themed activities and enjoy the creative and imaginative displays.</p>\r\n<p>These are some biggest festivals during the year, besides those, Ba Na Hills has arranged others like as Winter Festival, Food Festival, Halloween, Merry Christmas&hellip;..</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-fesstival.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"6\">6. When is the Best Time to Visit Ba Na Hills?</h3>\r\n<p>The best time to visit Ba Na Hills in Vietnam depends on your personal preferences and what kind of experience you&rsquo;re seeking. But we can help you find the season you love below:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Spring (Feb to May):</strong>&nbsp;Spring is generally an excellent time to visit. The weather is mild, with comfortable temperatures and lower humidity. The season of flowers with fresh forest creates beautiful landscapes. It&rsquo;s a great time to explore the natural beauty of Ba Na Hills.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Summer (June to August):</strong>&nbsp;Summer in Vietnam Central is hot and some days very hot, but don&rsquo;t worry, Ba Na Hills is a place that always keeps the temperature fresh and mid. We think if you looking for an easy trip then spring and summer is the best time to visit Ba Na Hills and enjoy the scene here</li>\r\n<li><strong>Autumn (September to Oct):</strong>&nbsp;Autumn offers pleasant weather with cooler temperatures compared to the summer months. But the autumn of Vietnam Central is stronger than others). It may rain and keep it for a long time on the day but you will find a very different experience there, it is considered a special thing in Ba Na Hills.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Winter (Nov to Jan):</strong>&nbsp;Winter in Ba Na Hills can be chilly, especially in the evenings, so be prepared for cooler temperatures. If you enjoy a colder climate and the possibility of seeing misty landscapes, winter can be a unique and atmospheric time to visit. But please note that it&rsquo;s may be floods and storms in Vietnam Central this season, so we had several days to cancel the tour in winter. But don&rsquo;t worry it does not mean every year.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-10.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"7\">7. Ba Na Hills Admission &amp; Ticket Fees</h3>\r\n<p><em>The price has been applied from 01/09/2023 until further notice</em></p>\r\n<h4 id=\"7.1\">7.1 Cable Car ticket</h4>\r\n<p><strong>Price only for Da Nang citizens:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Adults: 600.000 VND/pax</li>\r\n<li>Children 1m to 1m4: 500.000 VND/pax</li>\r\n<li>Children &lt;1m: Free</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Price for Travelers (Other Countries And Locations Out Of Danang City):</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Adults: 900.000 VND/pax</li>\r\n<li>Children 1m to 1m4: 750.000 VND/pax</li>\r\n<li>Children &lt;1m: Free</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Notes:</strong>&nbsp;If you are local (Danang citizens), please bring your ID to enjoy the privileged treatment when buying Ba Na Hill tickets. Plus, this Ba Na Hill station cable car price does not include food fees, entrance fees to some places or games in Ba Na such as the Wax Museum, or winning games at Fantasy Park. Those fees already include 10% VAT.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"7.2\">7.2 Ba Na Hills Cable Car Price For Combo (Cable Car Ticket and Lunch Buffet)</h4>\r\n<p>Most especially, you can choose to buy the following ticket for Ba Na Hills Cable Car Combo packages, which applied from 1/9/2023 &ndash; 31/12/2023:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Danang citizens</strong></p>\r\n<table class=\"table-blog\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th rowspan=\"2\">Options</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">Price</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Adult</th>\r\n<th>Children (1m to 1m4)</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cable car + lunch buffer</td>\r\n<td>950.000 VND</td>\r\n<td>700.000 VND</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cable car + Afternoon buffer</td>\r\n<td>1.150.000 VND</td>\r\n<td>850.000 VND</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cable car + Dinner buffer</td>\r\n<td>800.000 VND</td>\r\n<td>600.000 VND</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>Travelers (Other Countries And Locations Out Of Danang City)</strong></p>\r\n<table class=\"table-blog\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th rowspan=\"2\">Options</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">Price</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Adult</th>\r\n<th>Children (1m to 1m4)</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cable car + lunch buffer</td>\r\n<td>1.200.000 VND</td>\r\n<td>900.000 VND</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cable car + Afternoon buffer</td>\r\n<td>1.150.000 VND</td>\r\n<td>850.000 VND</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cable car + Dinner buffer</td>\r\n<td>800.000 VND</td>\r\n<td>600.000 VND</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h4 id=\"7.3\">7.3 What Is Included In Ba Na Hills Ticket Price?</h4>\r\n<p>If you are looking for, What services does the Ba Na Hill ticket price include? According to the regulation of the Ba Na Hills operating department, when a tourist buys a Ba Na Hills ticket from June to December, they can enjoy the following services:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2 way cable car trip</li>\r\n<li>The buyers can take part in different games in the Fantasy Park for free, including over 105 games and free games of legendary Knight Slide Games</li>\r\n<li>Vietnam funicular (mountain climbing train) service</li>\r\n<li>Ticket owners can visit the Flower Garden, Debay Wine Cellar (excluding wine), and the Golden Bridge (Da Nang).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-7.jpg\" alt=\"Is Bana Hills Worth It\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"8\">8. How to Get Tickets</h3>\r\n<p>Have many ways to get the Ba Na Hills ticket, you can see some ways below:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Get the ticket from us at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/\"><strong>Hoiantravel</strong></a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/\"><strong>VMTravel</strong></a>&nbsp;you can send a request or contact directly to us directly via WhatsApp: +84 399012553 (Ms.Trang), +84 91 9591234 (Mr. Benz) send you the ticket with the exact price is informed from Ba Na Hills.</li>\r\n<li>Get the ticket directly from the Ba Na Hills office, when you arrive at this place, come to the office ticket to buy the ticket by yourself, or you can buy it at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://banahills.sunworld.vn/en/\">Banahills.sunworld</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 id=\"9\">9. How To Get To Ba Na Hills</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"9.1\">9.1 How to Get to Ba Na Hills From Da Nang</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Small or big group tour:</strong>&nbsp;You can join a small group tour with full options like a speaking guide, high-quality transfer, door-to-door pick up at your hotel&hellip; with the best price&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/hoi-an-to-bana-hills-small-group-tour/\">Bana Hills Small Group Tour From Hoian</a></li>\r\n<li><strong>Private Car:</strong>&nbsp;You can also hire a private car or arrange for transportation through your accommodation. This option provides flexibility and comfort but may come at a higher cost</li>\r\n<li><strong>Taxi or Ride-Sharing:</strong>&nbsp;The most convenient but often more expensive option is to take a taxi or use ride-sharing services like Grab from Da Nang to Ba Na Hills. The ride will take approximately 40-60 minutes, depending on traffic.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Motorbike:</strong>&nbsp;you also can rent a motorbike to drive to Ba Na Hills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"9.2\">9.2 How to Get to Ba Na Hills From Hoi an</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Small or big group tour:</strong>&nbsp;You can join a small group tour with full options like a speaking guide, high-quality transfer, door-to-door pick up at your hotel&hellip;. with the best price in this link:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/hoi-an-to-bana-hills-small-group-tour/\">Ba Na Hills Small Group Tour from Da Nang, and Hoi An</a></li>\r\n<li><strong>Private Car:</strong>&nbsp;You can also hire a private car or arrange for transportation through your accommodation. This option provides flexibility and comfort but may come at a higher cost</li>\r\n<li><strong>The Cheapest Way to Do Ba Na Hills:</strong>&nbsp;If you looking for the best way to visit Ba Na Hills with high quality and good price, then a small group tour is the best solution, with this tour tour you not care about how to move from your hotel or get the information about the ticket, lunch, time our guide will provide you everything necessary during the trip</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-2.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"10\">10. How Long Do You Need at Ba Na Hills</h3>\r\n<p>You can spend 3-4 hours visiting The Golden Bridge and return to the center city, you also can spend a full day in this place exploring many exciting places in Ba Na Hills. The amount of time you need at Ba Na Hills can vary widely depending on your interests and how thoroughly you want to explore the attractions.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Day Trip:</strong>&nbsp;If you&rsquo;re planning a day trip to Ba Na Hills, you can typically spend around 6 to 8 hours there. This should allow you to experience many of the main attractions, take in the scenic views, enjoy a meal, and even catch some of the performances or events.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Full Exploration:</strong>&nbsp;For a more comprehensive exploration of Ba Na Hills, including visiting multiple attractions, enjoying various rides, and experiencing cultural shows, plan to spend a full day. This could require 10 to 12 hours or more</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/sunset-at-golden-bridge-ba-na-hills-tour/\"><strong>Ba Na Hills Sunset (overnight):</strong></a>&nbsp;If you choose to stay overnight, you can spread your exploration over two days. This provides a more relaxed pace, allowing you to enjoy both daytime and evening activities without rushing. You can explore the resort&rsquo;s attractions, enjoy evening entertainment, and experience the tranquil atmosphere of the mountain resort.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-1.jpg\" alt=\"bana hills in da nang\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"11\">11. Things You Should Know Before Your Trip to Ba Na Hills</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"11.1\">11.1 What to Wear to Ba Na Hills?</h4>\r\n<p>Dress comfortably and in layers, as the weather can change throughout the day. Consider wearing breathable clothing, and comfortable shoes for walking, and bring a light jacket or sweater, especially if you plan to stay until evening when it can get cooler. Modest attire is suitable for visiting cultural and religious sites within Ba Na Hills.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"11.2\">11.2 What Time Does Ba Na Hills Open?</h4>\r\n<p>Ba Na Hills typically opens in the morning, often around 7:00 AM or 8:00 AM. However, the exact opening time can vary depending on the season and day of the week. It&rsquo;s advisable to check the official Ba Na Hills website or contact them directly for the most up-to-date information on opening times.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"11.3\">11.3 Ba Na Hills Opening Hours?</h4>\r\n<p>Ba Na Hills&rsquo; opening hours can also vary based on the time of year and specific attractions within the complex. Generally, it closes in the late afternoon or early evening, around 5:00 PM to 6:00 PM. Once again, the official website or direct contact with Ba Na Hills is the best way to confirm the current opening hours.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"11.4\">11.4 Can You Drive to Ba Na Hills?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes, you can drive to Ba Na Hills, and there is parking available at the entrance. However, it&rsquo;s important to note that the primary means of transportation within Ba Na Hills is the cable car system, which transports visitors from the base to the resort complex at the top of the mountain.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"11.5\">11.5 Does Ba Na Hills Take Credit Cards?</h4>\r\n<p>Ba Na Hills generally accepts credit and debit cards for payments at various points within the resort complex, such as ticket counters, restaurants, and souvenir shops. However, it&rsquo;s a good practice to carry some cash (Vietnamese Dong) for smaller purchases or in case certain places may not accept cards. Be sure to check with specific vendors or locations for their payment options.</p>\r\n</div>', 'posts/December2023/T96CP6vbkqSbUKUJnqKg.png', 'is-bana-hills-worth-it-what-to-do-in-bana-hills-2024-2025', 'Ba Na Hills in Vietnam located in the Truong Son Mountains system near Da Nang, Vietnam, is a destination that effortlessly blends natural beauty, cultural heritage, and great attractions. This place is sought after by guests around the world.', 'Is Bana Hills Worth It? What To Do In Bana Hills 2024-2025', 'PUBLISHED', 1, '2023-12-28 21:15:42', '2023-12-28 21:15:42');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `author_id`, `category_id`, `title`, `seo_title`, `excerpt`, `body`, `image`, `slug`, `meta_description`, `meta_keywords`, `status`, `featured`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(16, 1, 1, 'Things To Do In Hoi An – 15 Exquisite Activities You Can’t Miss!', 'Things To Do In Hoi An – 15 Exquisite Activities You Can’t Miss!', 'Arriving in Hoi An in a stunning classic, we learned that this city offers the greatest experiences that anyone should have at least once in their lifetime. Watch the best things to do in Hoi An that meet the expectations of both domestic and foreign visitors here.', '<h3 id=\"1\">1. Best things to do in Hoi An &ndash; Top 10 attractions of tourism when coming to Hoi An</h3>\r\n<p>For the major part of Hoi An tourism is easily attracted by walking the Street&rsquo;s classic beauty with French and Asian influences. In other words, you can visit a lot of locations by making a reservation or renting a car. Its timeless beauty draws tourists who come to marvel at it; the world is changing and developing, but it&rsquo;s unique beauty remains unaffected. It is therefore a tourist attraction. Let&rsquo;s have a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/day-trip-from-da-nang-to-hoi-an/\"><strong>day trip from Da Nang to Hoi An.</strong></a></p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/things-to-do-in-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"things to do in hoian\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.1\">1.1 Walk around the Old Town</h4>\r\n<p>One of the most fascinating locations in Old Town is the Walking Street City, which opened in 2004 and is located along the Hoai Rivers on Tran Phu Street, Nguyen Hue Street, C&ocirc;ng Nu Ngoc Hoa Street, and the front of Spare.</p>\r\n<p>It brings traditions of Vietnam&rsquo;s culture full of beauty. Tourists can find restaurants, coffee shops, gift shops, shops selling handicrafts, and other establishments that uphold the Hoi An standard along the street.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, Walk Street embraces cultural events, particularly those involving the arts, like water puppet shows and music concerts. During this time, cars are not driven on the street to make room for people who want to stroll, shop, or just take in the breathtaking scenery.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/walking-hoi-an-ancient-town.jpg\" alt=\"Walk around the Old Town\"></div>\r\n<p><strong>When visiting, take note of the following:</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"notes-location-blog\">\r\n<div><em><strong>Address:</strong>&nbsp;Tran Phu Street, Nguyen Hue Street, C&ocirc;ng N? Ng?c Hoa Street</em></div>\r\n<div><em><strong>Opening hours:</strong>&nbsp;each day, 7am to 11am and 15pm to 21 pm or 21: 30 pm in the summer</em></div>\r\n<div><em><strong>Ticket price:</strong>&nbsp;The cost of the tickets consists of two categories: international and Vietnamese tourist tickets</em></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.2\">1.2 Visit Japanese Covered Bridge</h4>\r\n<p>A Japanese person who raised funds erected the Chua Cau (or Japanese Covered Bridge), which is a symbol of Hoi An Ancient Town, in the 17th century. As a result, the bridge blended Vietnamese and Japanese styles. One of Vietnam&rsquo;s most significant historical sites and cultural icons, Chua Cau was inducted as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1999.</p>\r\n<p>The bridge, which was made up of a bridge and a temple section, was a unique construction. The main door has three Chinese words for the bridge portion, which was constructed on wood and numerous negative and positive pantile roofs. The god Bac De Tran Vo, who guarded craftsmen and entrepreneurs, was partially represented by the pagoda.</p>\r\n<p>An old legend about the Namazu monster and its remains in Vietnam was told at Pagoda Bridge. To keep the monster from affecting all citizens, they constructed a bridge. Nowadays, Chua Cau is a popular destination that draws many tourists from both domestic and foreign countries these days.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Japanese-Covered-Bridge.jpg\" alt=\"Visit Japanese Covered Bridge\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.3\">1.3 Explore the local countryside</h4>\r\n<p>It introduces traditional Vietnamese culture. The majority of the population here is made up of farmers, cultivators, fishermen and breeders. Numerous well-known traditional trade villages exist, including the vegetable village of Tra Que, the rice paper village of Cam Le, and the Thanh Ha terracotta village</p>\r\n<p>In addition to being a traditional village, the nearby Hoi An village has a lot of room to grow in terms of agriculture and tourism. This kind of travel is growing similar to experiencing villages for ecotourism.</p>\r\n<p>Visitors come here to take in the picturesque surroundings of the small, rural community. If you want to go but anyone visits with you, you can go on the&nbsp;<strong>Hoi An Cycling Tour</strong>&nbsp;with lots of strangers, but it&rsquo;s great to be able to stop and take pictures and appreciate the scenery.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-countryside.jpg\" alt=\"Explore the local countryside\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.4\">1.4 Visit Tra Que Village</h4>\r\n<p>Vegetables are the specialty of Tra Que village in Hoi An, Quang Nam province. It is located between the De Vong River and the Tra Que Swamp, roughly 3 kilometers from the Northwest&rsquo;s capital. Tra Que&rsquo;s Vegetable Village is a popular destination for ecotourism.</p>\r\n<p>When visitors arrive, they see a verdant vegetable field, take in the pure air, and discover how the locals use the growing plants. Furthermore, tourists participate in exciting experiential activities such as cycling, rowing, and vegetable picking.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Boating:</strong>&nbsp;Tourists can rent a boat and paddle around the Tra Que lagoon, taking in the picturesque views of the verdant vegetable fields and quiet village surroundings.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cycling:</strong>&nbsp;Guests can rent bicycles and ride them around the village, stopping to explore its narrow streets, historic homes, and verdant vegetable gardens.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Picking vegetables:</strong>&nbsp;Visitors to the garden are able to take part in a live vegetable-picking experience. Visitors can enjoy dishes made with fresh vegetables and gain a better understanding of the vegetable-growing process by participating in this engaging activity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>People who enjoy being in natural and cultural settings will find the&nbsp;<strong>Tra Que Village Tour</strong>&nbsp;to be a perfect location. Once you get to the village, you can take in the delicious food made with fresh vegetables and explore a small, tranquil town.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Tra-Que-Village.jpg\" alt=\"Explore the local countryside\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.5\">1.5 Join a Cooking Class</h4>\r\n<p>Travelers to Vietnam are drawn to Hoi An because of its historic homes, colorful lantern decorations, and mouthwatering food. Taking a cooking class is a fantastic activity if you have plans to visit Hoi An.</p>\r\n<p>Cooking classes come in a variety of styles and prices to suit every interest and budget. Among the Cooking Classes are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Vietnam Traditional Cooking Class:</strong>&nbsp;Learn how to prepare staple Vietnamese dishes like pho and bun bo Hue in this class.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cooking class in Tra Que village:</strong>&nbsp;You will learn how to prepare fresh vegetables grown in Tra Que village during this class.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Seafood Class:</strong>&nbsp;Learn how to prepare fresh seafood dishes like ink salad and seafood flour-based meals in the seafood class.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Identify your pastime:</strong>&nbsp;Do you want to prepare modern Vietnamese cuisine, traditional Vietnamese cuisine, cuisine from other Vietnamese religions, or just Hoi An cuisine?<br>Reading other people&rsquo;s comments about their experiences in the Cooking Class helps you learn about the class&rsquo;s quality and leadership.</p>\r\n<p>You can discover the ideal of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/hoi-an-cooking-class/\"><strong>Hoi An Cooking Class</strong></a>&nbsp;with a little research to help you experience Vietnamese cuisine and leave a lasting impression.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-Cooking-Class.jpg\" alt=\"Join a Cooking Class\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.6\">1.6 Take a trip to the My Son Sanctuary</h4>\r\n<p>One of the most significant relics of the Champa civilization and a well-known tourist destination in Vietnam is My Son Sanctuary, which draws thousands of visitors each year. In 1999, the location received recognition as a UNESCO World Heritage Site. In My Son&rsquo;s Sanctuary, burning coal and stones were used to construct the temples and towers.</p>\r\n<p>The towers and temples at My Son Sanctuary are architectural representations of the Champa civilization&rsquo;s remarkable historical growth. Sophisticated building methods and materials were used to construct the temples and towers, and Champa art was infused into the decorative details.</p>\r\n<p>A place with sacred holy places and mysteries behind unique structures will bring you a new and exciting experience. You can refer to the specific article for all the information to have a memorable&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/my-son-small-group-tour-half-day-from-hoi-an/\"><strong>My Son Sanctuary Tour from Hoian</strong></a>&nbsp;experience.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/My-Son-Sanctuary-1.jpg\" alt=\"Take a trip to the My Son Sanctuary\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.7\">1.7 Check out the nightlife and shop at the Lantern Market</h4>\r\n<p>A market of ornamental, multicolored lanterns is one of the attractions of Hoi An&rsquo;s nightlife. Situated approximately 1km from the central ancient area, it is in the An Cuu area. From afternoon to evening, the lantern market is open. This is the perfect location to purchase mementos for your loved ones, savor the regional fare, and take in the vibrant atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p>There are many well-liked activities here that you should check out when you get to Hoi An. I hope your trip to the Hoi An lantern market is enjoyable and unforgettable.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-lantern-market.jpg\" alt=\"Lantern Market\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.8\">1.8 Relax at Beaches</h4>\r\n<p>A beach is a need in hot weather conditions. An Bang Beach is also a fantastic option. The beach is a great place to unwind, go swimming, participate in water sports, and discover the nearby fishing community. You can rent a chair or an umbrella here to unwind after engaging in a variety of outdoor activities including water skiing, boating, or strolling along the shore. Watching the sunset also produces a beautiful scene, with the crimson sun like a massive fireball as it gets closer.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-beach.jpg\" alt=\"Hoi An Beach\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.9\">1.9 Have a Boat Trip</h4>\r\n<p>One of the best things you can experience in Hoi An is a boat trip on the Hoai River. The Hoai River is a branch of the Thu Bon River in Hoi An, located in Hoi An City. Winding through the heart of the ancient town, the Hoai River plays a crucial role in the lives of Hoi An&rsquo;s residents and the city&rsquo;s development. During a boat ride, you may observe Hoi An&rsquo;s historic homes and many local fishermen doing their work on the river.</p>\r\n<p>One of the most fascinating things to do is to light a drop flower lantern, a flower lantern traditional Hoi An made of paper or another material and illuminated by candles or flashlights. Visitors can write messages on the flower lanterns before releasing them to float down the river. The popular belief is that desires will be granted by being sent to paradise.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-boat.jpg\" alt=\"Hoi An Boat\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.10\">1.10 Visit Coconut Cam Thanh village</h4>\r\n<p>In Hoi An, the village of Coconut Cam Thanh is referred to as Coconut Kingdom. Coconuts are used for building materials, crafts, and more than just drinking water, cooking oil, and candies.</p>\r\n<p>The Coconut Cam Thanh village is a delicious destination that draws travelers from all over the country and the world. When visitors enter, they will experience the tranquility of the village, learn about the distinctive features and customs of the area, and savor the cuisine made from coconuts.</p>\r\n<p>Visitors should give it a try when they visit Hoi An at least once in their lifetime. For all the details you need to have an amazing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/cam-thanh-coconut-village-private-tour-from-hoi-an/\"><strong>Cam Thanh Coconut Village Tour</strong></a>, see the relevant article.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-coconut-village.jpg\" alt=\"Visit Coconut Cam Thanh village\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.11\">1.11 Explore Tan Ky Family House</h4>\r\n<p>The Tan Ky Family House in Hoi An was a historic home constructed in the 19th century that was modeled after the wooden houses of the Tan Ky district in the province of Nghe An. The house address is 101 Nguyen Thai Hoc Street, Hoi An City, Quang Nam Province. The house is airy, solidly constructed, and made of ironwood. Cone-shaped tiles made of yin and yang cover the roof. The house has sturdy wood walls with a sound construction. The wood door has a straightforward but reliable design. The wood column system of the house has a sturdy construction.</p>\r\n<p>The house&rsquo;s interior design is understated but elegant. Every household utensil is crafted from wood and features elaborate carvingsThe Tan Ky family home in Hoi An is a priceless example of old architecture. The house is evidence of how different Vietnamese regions&rsquo; cultures have influenced one another</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tan-ky-old-house.jpg\" alt=\"Visit Coconut Cam Thanh village\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.12\">1.12 Grab a coffee</h4>\r\n<p>Vietnam loves its coffee, and Hoi An is no different. Hoi An coffee is known for its distinct flavor and strong aroma due to its hand-roasted and ground beans. Since coffee is made with hot, boiling water, it has an amazing flavor.</p>\r\n<p>There are two primary varieties of coffee in Hoi An: milk coffee and black coffee. In Hoi An, black coffee is the most widely consumed variety. Hoi An&rsquo;s black coffee is strongly scented and has a rich, bitter taste due to its intense roasting. Condensed milk is added to coffee to create milk coffee. Hoi An milk coffee tastes sweet and fragrant. Furthermore, Hoi An offers a variety of other coffee varieties, including weasel coffee, egg coffee, and coconut coffee</p>\r\n<p>One aspect of Hoi An culture is coffee. Coffee is typically consumed in the morning, afternoon, or evening by Hoi An people. Coffee serves as a gathering spot, a means of communication, and a means of sharing.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-coffee.jpg\" alt=\"Grab a coffee in hoian\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"notes-location-blog\"><strong>Here are a few well-known cafes in Hoi An:</strong>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><em><strong>Faifo Coffee:</strong>&nbsp;This large, open coffee shop is situated in the heart of the historic town of Hoi An.</em></div>\r\n<div><em><strong>Moc Coffee:</strong>&nbsp;Rustic wooden tables and chairs adorn the cafe&rsquo;s compact but welcoming interior</em></div>\r\n<div><em><strong>Four Seasons Coffee:</strong>&nbsp;Housed in an old Hoi An house, this coffee shop boasts a serene and antiquated atmosphere</em></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.13\">1.13 Get a suit made</h4>\r\n<p>When visiting the historic house, getting a suit made in Hoi An is a fascinating experience that you shouldn&rsquo;t pass up. Tailor shops are fast, have reasonable prices, and have qualified staff.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Optional clothing materials:</strong>&nbsp;Prior to purchasing a suit, you must decide on a material that will work for your needs and interests. There are plenty of clothing options in Hoi An, including silk, cotton, and linen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The clothing&rsquo;s optional shape:</strong>&nbsp;Travelers can choose clothing shapes based on their interests or use their suggestions. There are many different designs available at the Hoi An tailor shop, ranging from classic to modern shapes.</li>\r\n<li>Optional size: Visitors tell store clerks how big their bodies are so they may make a suit that fits them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/suit-made-in-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"suit made in hoian\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"notes-location-blog\"><strong>Here are a few upscale addresses in Hoi An where you can get suits made:</strong>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><em><strong>Minh Chau tailor business:</strong>&nbsp;Hoi An at 28 Nguyen Thai Hoc streets</em></div>\r\n<div><em><strong>Hoi An&rsquo;s Ao Dai tailor business:</strong>&nbsp;147 Tran Phu streets</em></div>\r\n<div><em><strong>Kim Oanh:</strong>&nbsp;Hoi An, 56 Nguyen Thai Hoc Street</em></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.14\">1.14 Day trip to Hue Imperial City</h4>\r\n<p>There are certain locations in Hoi An that visitors ought to visit at least once in their lifetime. Tourists should go to Hue Imperial City for the day. Hue Imperial City is located in the center of Thua Thien Hue province. It was designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1993. The historic capital of Hue is a popular travel destination that draws both domestic and foreign visitors.</p>\r\n<p>To learn about Vietnam&rsquo;s golden age&rsquo;s history, culture, and architecture, you can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/hoi-an-hue-hoi-an-tour/\"><strong>join Hue City Tour from Hoi An</strong></a>&nbsp;for a curated itinerary with a door-to-door service and knowledge guide.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hue-city-tour.jpg\" alt=\"Day trip to Hue Imperial City\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.15\">1.15 Day trip to Bana Hills and Golden Bridge</h4>\r\n<p>If you travel around Da Nang, you can consider engaging in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/hoi-an-to-bana-hills-small-group-tour/\"><strong>Day Trip to Ba Na Hills from Hoian</strong></a>. The tour offers a chance to conquer the longest wire cable car in the world and admire various unique architectural works, including the ancient French Village and a dreamy flower garden. Do not forget to stroll around the &ldquo;Golden Bridge&rdquo;, one of the world&rsquo;s most spectacular pedestrian bridges. Moreover, Ba Na Hills offers plenty of thrilling activities for the family in Fantasy Park.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/bana-fesstival.jpg\" alt=\"Day trip to Bana Hills and Golden Bridge\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"2\">2. Best time to visit Hoi An?</h3>\r\n<p>The weather is the key factor when planning a travel trip. Although Hoi An always keeps its ancient beauty any time of the year, learning about its weather will enhance your experience. To be well-prepared for clothes and itinerary, you can visit the comprehensive guidance about the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/best-time-to-visit-hoi-an/\"><strong>Best time to visit Hoi An!</strong></a></p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.1\">2.1 Dry Season</h4>\r\n<p>During the dry season, February through April are the best time to visit Hoi An. This time of year in Hoi An, the weather is lovely and sunny with minimal rain, making it ideal for sightseeing and exploration. It is also rather dry.</p>\r\n<p>Travelers can enjoy the breathtaking scenery of the Hoi An ancient during this time of year, which features red lanterns, tiny alleyways constructed of laterites, and an antique house with a historic sign. Together, these qualities produce a serene and lovely scene. Furthermore, Hoi An was home to a number of customary events during this period, including the Flower Lantern Festival and the Am Duong Festival. Visitors can take part in the celebration to get a taste of the Hoi An people&rsquo;s culture and character.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/best-time-to-visit-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"Best time to visit Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.2\">2.2 Wet Season</h4>\r\n<p>During the wet season, September through November are the best time to visit Hoi An. Hoi An experienced somewhat cool, breezy weather during this time of year, with typical highs of 25 to 30 degrees. There isn&rsquo;t much rain&mdash;only 15 to 20 days per month.</p>\r\n<p>Travelers will notice Hoi An&rsquo;s distinctions at this time of day, including its little alleyways lined by verdant trees and its stunning crimson rain. Everything works together to produce a serene and lovely atmosphere. In addition, Hoi An was hosting a plethora of unique festivals around this time, including the Nghinh Ong and Can Ngu festivals. Visitors can take part in this celebration to get a taste of the Hoi An people&rsquo;s culture and character.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"3\">3. What to do in Hoi An at night</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.1\">3.1 Release a paper lantern and make a wish</h4>\r\n<p>When you visit the Hoai River, you know what to do on Hoi An at night. One of the activities is to draw flower lanterns. Making wishes and releasing paper lanterns are two of the Hoi An people&rsquo;s customs. This event frequently takes place during celebrations like the Lantern Festival, the Yin Yang Festival, and&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>You can purchase paper lanterns from souvenir shops in the historic town of Hoi An if you want to take part in the tradition of releasing lanterns and making wishes. A paper lamp costs between 5,000 and 10,000 VND.</p>\r\n<p>You can write your wish on paper and hang it from the paper lamp after purchasing one. Following that, you have the option to release paper lanterns from the boat or into the Hoai River.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/paper-lantern.jpg\" alt=\"paper lantern - best things to do in hoi an\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.2\">3.2 Grab a drink and enjoy Hoi An old town</h4>\r\n<p>Hoi An at night, choosing a beverage shop is an ideal way to enjoy Hoi An Old Town. It is highly recommended that you sample the local beverages when visiting the historic town of Hoi An.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/enjoy-Hoi-An-old-town.jpg\" alt=\"enjoy Hoi An old town\"></div>\r\n<p><strong>Here are some ideas for you to consider while sipping a drink and exploring the historic town of Hoi An:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Savor your coffee:</strong>&nbsp;In Hoi An, coffee is a popular beverage. In the old town, coffee shops are everywhere. Hoi An&rsquo;s coffee is made in a traditional manner and has an amazing flavor.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Savor your tea:</strong>&nbsp;In Hoi An, tea is also a preferred beverage. Several varieties of tea are available in the old town&rsquo;s souvenir shops. Hoi An&rsquo;s tea is made with only pure teas, which have a delightfully light flavor.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Savor additional beverages:</strong>&nbsp;You can enjoy other beverages in Hoi An besides coffee and tea, like beer and juice: Several varieties of fruit juices are available at Hoi An Old Town gift shops.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Iced Milk Coffee:</strong>&nbsp;A popular beverage in Hoi An is iced milk. When tourists visit and should try it once in their life</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.3\">3.3 Walk along the Thu Bon River and shop at Night Market</h4>\r\n<p>Numerous night markets can be found along the Thu Bon River, with the majority of them being in large cities like Hoi An and Tam Ky. These night markets offer a wide variety of goods and are frequently open from evening until late. from footwear, apparel, and trinkets to snacks.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-at-night.jpg\" alt=\"Hoi An at Night\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.4\">3.4 Coffee and Night Bars</h4>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re wondering what to do in Hoi An at night, coffee shops and nightclubs are great options. It is an essential component of the community of Hoi An. Hoi An is home to a large number of well-known bars that provide a variety of drinks, including wine, beer, cocktails, and more.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-best-restaurant.jpg\" alt=\"Hoi An at Night\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"4\">4. How to get Hoi An in Vietnam?</h3>\r\n<p>By Air: Hoi An has no Airport, therefore you can arrive in Da Nang first. The nearest airport to Hoi An is Da Nang International Airport. You can book a flight to Da Nang from major cities in Vietnam and various international destinations. From Da Nang, Hoi An is about a 30-40 minute drive away. Taxis, buses, or private car hires are available at the airport for the journey to Hoi An.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.1\">4.1 Da Nang to Hoi An</h4>\r\n<p>For a curated itinerary, knowledge tour guide, and door-to-door service, you can choose a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/day-trip-from-da-nang-to-hoi-an/\"><strong>Hoi An Day Trip from Da Nang</strong></a>. With the tour, you will be worry-free to explore the ancient beauty of Hoi An Old Town and engage in interesting activities here.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/da-nang-to-hoi-an.jpg\" alt=\"Da nang to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.2\">4.2 Hue to Hoi An</h4>\r\n<p>Hue is away from Hoi An, approximately about 127 kilometers. Choose a Hoi An Day Trip from Hue to discover Hoi An ancient town from the ancient capital of Hue. The tour brings an opportunity to conquer Hai Van Pass &ndash; one of the most beautiful coastal routes in the world and stop at other landmarks in Central Vietnam.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hue-to-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"Hue to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"5\">5. Is Hoi An worth visiting?</h3>\r\n<p>Without a doubt, Hoi An is a truly worthwhile destination that everyone should visit at least once. Hoi An is a stunning location with historic buildings and architecture, as well as numerous festivals that showcase the locals&rsquo; ability to live like flower lanterns. In addition, a city brings beautiful old villages and is especially not influenced by the advancement of society, bearing a strong mark of historical identity. Hopefully, more people will be able to visit Hoi An and take in the stunning location and culture.</p>\r\n<p><em>Hoi An is awesome! The old streets with pretty lanterns are like stepping back in time. Vibrant culture, diverse cuisine, and friendly locals make Hoi An more charming and peaceful in the hustle and bustle of life nowadays. Everything about Hoi An is just so &ldquo;vintage&rdquo; and makes you feel like you&rsquo;re in a special place in the 21st century.</em></p>', 'posts/December2023/ZLXHKaSAPUEwKELJVEEQ.png', 'things-to-do-in-hoi-an-15-exquisite-activities-you-can-t-miss', 'Arriving in Hoi An in a stunning classic, we learned that this city offers the greatest experiences that anyone should have at least once in their lifetime. Watch the best things to do in Hoi An that meet the expectations of both domestic and foreign visitors here.', 'Things To Do In Hoi An – 15 Exquisite Activities You Can’t Miss!', 'PUBLISHED', 1, '2023-12-28 21:16:39', '2023-12-28 21:16:39');
