areast;\">&nbsp;</span></span>show takes place at 09:30 am or 14h30 and lasts about 45 minutes to 1 hour.<span class=\"apple-converted-space\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast;\">&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">DO NOT MISS IT!</span></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-indent: 18.0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #1e4da5;\">Included</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">New Modern Private Car<br>English-speaking tour guide<br>Entrance fees<br>Bottled drinking water<br>FOC for children<br></span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #ff6600;\">Excluded</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Meals<br>Personal Fee</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 0, 'my-son-sanctuary-half-day-from-hoi-an-private-tour', 71, 40, 32, 29, 25, 22, 20, 19, 100),
(14, 'Cam Thanh Coconut Village From Hoi An – Private Tour', 'Cam Thanh Coconut Village From Hoi An – Private Tour', 'Hoi An', 'sightseeing', '2024-01-18 08:24:17', '2024-01-22 10:11:17', '[]', 'tours/January2024/zHyyPc83MOrrn0NaxXU6.jpeg', '<div class=\"WordSection1\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #1e4da5;\">Tour Highlights</span></strong></h3>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Discover Cam Thanh Coconut Village rich culture and natural beauty</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Experience fishing with local people</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Learn how to row a basket, immerse yourself in the idyllic life here</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #1e4da5;\">Tour Itinerary</span></strong></h3>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>At 8:00 am or 1:00 pm:</strong><span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>Our driver and tour guide will pick you up at the lobby of your hotel in Hoi An. It will 20 minute before you arrive in Cam Thanh.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Take a basket boat transferring to Cam Thanh water coconut village. Learn about the daily life of Vietnamese fishermen, their families and their community. On the trip, the boatman will take coconut leaves to make amazing natural ornaments such as hats, rings, glasses&hellip; These lovely ornaments will be then given to you as a gift. You will surely experience the feeling of floating on the waves of water and join an equally fun basket boat race between the baskets together in the cheering and bustling drum music.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Board on boat and commence cruising on the Cua Dai River. Join in local fisherman on the river and experience rounding net or casting net. Coconut forest is a very unique ecoregion, with a beautiful mangrove forest, is the habitat of many precious animals such as crabs, shrimps, fishes and shellfishes.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Local people will teach you how to paddle the Vietnamese unique bamboo basket boat. You will hear stories of past wars and the harsh conditions that soldiers have to endure.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Relax and transfer back the hotel. Ends tour.<strong><span style=\"color: #1e4da5;\"><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></span></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #1e4da5;\">Included</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Private car with high quality<br>English speaking guide<br>Entrance fees<br>Basket boat<br>Petrol<br>Road tolls</span></p>', 1, 'cam-thanh-coconut-village-from-hoi-an-private-tour', 53, 30, 24, 21, 19, 17, 15, 14, NULL),
(15, 'Sunset At Golden Bridge- Ba Na Hills Private Tour', 'Sunset At Golden Bridge- Ba Na Hills Private Tour', 'Hoi An', 'sightseeing', '2024-01-18 08:27:18', '2024-01-18 08:27:18', '[]', 'tours/January2024/kJYOybOQlMWAYg5uysar.jpg', '<div class=\"WordSection1\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #1e4da5;\">Tour Itinerary</span></strong></h3>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>At 3:00 pm:</strong><span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>Our driver and tour guide will pick you up at your hotel in Hoi An. If you are staying in Da Nang, please be ready in your hotel&rsquo;s lobby at 3:30 pm</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Upon arriving in Ba Na Hills, you will enjoy a height of more than 1,480m, watching the panoramic view of Ba Na mountain with modern cable car system.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Don&rsquo;t forget to take photos if the sunset on the horizon when you set foot on the Golden Bridge.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Continue to the top of the mountain, to explore the<span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><strong>French Colonial station, visiting French Village.</strong></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\">Have a buffet dinner of European cuisine and enjoy great draft beer made and being served only in Ba Na Hills.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>At 7.00 pm:</strong><span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>Get on a cable car to return to the private car at the foot of the hill</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><strong>At 9.00 pm:</strong><span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>Our driver and tour guide will drop you off your hotel in Da Nang/Hoi An</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; color: #333333; mso-ansi-language: #1000; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #1e4da5;\">Included</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">High-quality vehicle<br>English speaking tour guide<br>Cable Car ticket<br>Dinner Buffet</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; color: #ff6600;\">Excluded</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Personal expenses</span></p>', 0, 'sunset-at-golden-bridge-ba-na-hills-private-tour', 125, 83, 72, 67, 62, 58, 55, NULL, NULL),
(16, 'Tra Que Village – Herb & Vegetable Farming', 'Tra Que Village – Herb & Vegetable Farming', 'Hoi An', 'sightseeing', '2024-01-18 08:30:16', '2024-01-18 08:30:16', '[]', 'tours/January2024/MP03V3gWDK2zlNEYZtDn.jpg', '<h3 style=\"margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: \'inherit\',serif; color: #1e4da5;\">Tour Itinerary</span></strong></h3>\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',sans-serif;\">To start off your<span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><strong>Tra Que Village Tour,</strong><span class=\"apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>we will take a scenic bike ride out to a farm in the area &ndash; exercise is a great way to kickstart your day! Once we arrive, you will receive an introduction to the historical past of the village. In this short but informative lesson, you will learn about the cultivation process as well as the discovering of these vegetables use in traditional Vietnamese medicine.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: #333333; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',sans-serif;\">Afterwards, it&rsquo;s time for you to join the farmers! You will take a trip around the vegetable garden and assist in fertilising and preparing the land using seaweed from the local lake. Other farming activities include raking, sowing, picking greens and others depending on the day! After enjoying your time experiencing what farming at Tra Que is like, it will be time to prepare some authentic meals with a local family. You&rsquo;ll get to enjoy local specialities like Tam Huu (spring rolls) and Banh Xeo (central Vietnams traditional pancake). Finally, after enjoying your food 